Interface CampsViewer

All Known Implementing Classes:
StaffView, StudentView
public interface CampsViewer
The CampsViewer interface defines methods for viewing and searching camps based on various criteria. This interface is intended to be implemented by classes that require functionality to display camp information in different contexts.

  • Method Details

    • defaultCampsView

      boolean defaultCampsView()
      Displays a default view of all camps.
      Returns:
      true if there are camps to display, false otherwise.

    • searchByCampName

      void searchByCampName()
      Provides functionality to search camps by their name. This method typically prompts the user to enter the name of a camp and displays the matching results.

    • searchByCampDetails

      void searchByCampDetails()
      Allows searching of camps based on specific details like location, date, etc. This method typically prompts the user to enter search criteria and displays camps that match these criteria.

    • searchByCampDuration

      void searchByCampDuration()
      Enables the searching of camps based on their duration. This method typically prompts the user to select or enter a camp duration and displays camps that match this duration.
